# Notification Module Rules

References:

- docs/product-requirements.md
- docs/user-flows.md
- docs/api-specification.md

---

# Module Purpose

Responsibilities:

- User Notifications
- System Notifications
- Notification History
- Notification Delivery
- Notification Preferences

Notifications improve user engagement but must never affect core business logic.

---

# Core Principle

Notifications are informational.

Business processes must not depend on notifications.

---

Bad

Order Approved

↓

Send Notification

↓

Update Balance

---

Good

Order Approved

↓

Update Balance

↓

Create Notification

---

# Notification Types

Use enums.

Examples:

OrderApproved

OrderRejected

WithdrawalCreated

WithdrawalApproved

WithdrawalRejected

WithdrawalCompleted

SystemAnnouncement

---

Never hardcode strings.

---

# Notification Entity

Suggested Fields

- Id
- UserId
- Type
- Title
- Message
- IsRead
- CreatedAt
- ReadAt

---

# Source Of Truth

Notifications table is the source of truth.

Do not generate notifications dynamically.

Persist all notifications.

---

# Delivery Channels

MVP

✓ In-App Notifications

Future

- Email
- SMS
- Push Notification
- Telegram
- Zalo

---

# Notification Creation Rules

Notifications should be created after:

Order Approved

Order Rejected

Withdrawal Created

Withdrawal Approved

Withdrawal Rejected

Withdrawal Completed

---

Notifications should not be created for every minor event.

---

# Read Status Rules

Default

```text id="j8q2mc"
IsRead = false
```

---

User may:

Mark as Read

Mark All as Read

---

Never delete notifications automatically.

---

# Notification Ownership

Notification belongs to:

One User

---

Users can only access:

Their own notifications.

---

# Security Rules

User must never access:

Other users' notifications.

---

Admin announcements may be broadcast.

---

# System Announcements

Future Feature

Suggested Fields

- Title
- Message
- ActiveFrom
- ActiveTo

---

Visible to all users.

---

# Frontend Rules

Notification Bell

Display:

Unread Count

Recent Notifications

---

Notifications Page

Features:

- List Notifications
- Mark Read
- Mark All Read

---

Frontend must not:

Generate notifications

Calculate unread counts

---

# Required Endpoints

GET

/api/v1/notifications

---

GET

/api/v1/notifications/unread-count

---

POST

/api/v1/notifications/{id}/read

---

POST

/api/v1/notifications/read-all

---

# Required Commands

MarkNotificationReadCommand

MarkAllNotificationsReadCommand

CreateNotificationCommand

---

# Required Queries

GetNotificationsQuery

GetUnreadNotificationCountQuery

---

# Logging Rules

Log:

✓ Notification Created

✓ Notification Read

✓ Notification Delivery Failure

---

Never log:

✗ Personal content unnecessarily

✗ Sensitive user information

---

# Performance Rules

Indexes

- user_id
- is_read
- created_at

---

Pagination required.

Never return all notifications.

---

# Testing Requirements

✓ Notification Creation

✓ Read Notification

✓ Read All Notifications

✓ Unread Count

✓ User Isolation

✓ Pagination

---

# Documentation Rules

If notification flow changes:

Update:

- product-requirements.md
